value.value: Records describing the process required to capture, enter, store, and retrieve data in a clinical trial.
Records describing the Adjudication Committee's evaluation process of key events in a clinical trial.

label.value: Clinical Trial Central Laboratory Certification Document

value.value: Records detailing the certification by an authorized accrediting body of a central laboratory indicating their competence to participate in a given clinical trial.
Records pertaining to the core trial of a clinical trial.
Records detailing the correspondence and decisions regarding dose escalation during a clinical trial.
Records that contain information pertaining to the finances of a clinical trial.
Records certifying legal protection in the event of any unforeseen adverse circumstance arising during the course of a clinical trial.

label.value: Clinical Trial Independent Data Monitoring Committee Charter

value.value: Records describing the purpose and operation of the Independent Data Monitoring Committee (IDMC).
Records detailing the availability of compensation to a trial subject for injuries related to their participation in the trial.

label.value: Clinical Trial Interactive Response Technology Documentation

value.value: Records pertaining to the interactive response technology used in the clinical trial.

label.value: Clinical Trial Interfacility Standardization Method Document

value.value: Records confirming the ability of two or more facilities to achieve consistent results between facilities when performing same test or procedure.
Records pertaining to an investigator site in a clinical trial.

label.value: Clinical Trial Laboratory Sample Detail Documentation

value.value: Records pertaining to the collection, storage, shipping, tracking, location, and retention of a laboratory sample.

label.value: Clinical Trial Management Communication and Tracking Document

value.value: Records pertaining to the management and tracking of a clinical trial.
Records detailing communications, agreements, significant discussions, or relevant information related to clinical trial management.
Records detailing the progress of clinical trial activities.
Records that detail the roles of trial members, their contact details, and the structure of the team of a clinical trial.
Records pertaining to the recording of shipping, handling, and labeling of products and supplies that are not related to a investigational product (IP).

label.value: Clinical Trial Non-Investigational Product Supplies Documentation of Return

value.value: Records that account for the return of any supplies used during the trail that are not related to the investigational product.

label.value: Clinical Trial Notification of Termination Document

value.value: Records that notify regulatory authorities of the termination of a clinical trial.

label.value: Clinical Trial Notification to Investigators of Safety Information Document

value.value: Records that describe the notification to investigators of all findings related to the safety of a clinical trial. This may contain important information on serious adverse events and/or safety concerns that could adversely affect the safety of subjects, impact the conduct of the trial, or alter the approval/favorable opinion of the institutional review board (IRB)/independent ethics committee (IEC) to continue the trial.
Records that detail any non-compliance or deviations from a clinical study's protocol.
Records pertaining to the regulatory approval of a clinical trial.
Records that track the regulatory activities during the course of a clinical trial.
Records pertaining to the safety reporting, monitoring and notification within a clinical trial.
Records that describe the feasibility of a specific site for a given clinical study protocol
Records verifying that all requirements to initiate a clinical trial site are completed and trial participation may begin.

label.value: Clinical Trial Site Management Tracking Document

value.value: Records that track the site management activities during the course of a clinical trial.

label.value: Clinical Trial Site Personnel Contact Document

value.value: Records that contains the contact information for members of the clinical trial team.
Records detailing both the selection process of a clinical trial site, and the description of the chosen site.

label.value: Clinical Trial Site Task Assignment Document

value.value: Records tracking the task designations made by the principal investigator to trial personnel.

label.value: Clinical Trial Site Training Completion Document

value.value: Records that verify completion of clinical trial site training for the site medical investigator and his/her staff.
Records used to document data on a specific trial subject.

label.value: Clinical Trial Supply Storage Condition Document

value.value: Records that contain the description of the setting and circumstances for storing supplies used in a clinical trial.
Records pertaining to the storage of supplies, including the investigational product, used in clinical trials.

label.value: Clinical Trial Supply Storage Excursion Document

value.value: Records that describe deviations from the clinical trial supply storage plan.

label.value: Data Definitions for Analysis Dataset Document

value.value: Records that define and describe the programming logic required to transform a raw dataset to an analysis dataset.
Records of communications pertaining to data management.
Records pertaining to data management.
Records pertaining to the management, acquisition, validation, storage, protection, and processing of data.
Records detailing the operating procedures for the acquisition, validation, storage, protection, and processing of data in a clinical trial.
Records pertaining to any activities logged that relate to data management during the course of a clinical trial.
Records pertaining to the certification by an authorized accrediting body confirming the successful implantation, and accurate functionality of a data validation program.
Records pertaining to the completion of a data validation test.
Records that contain the management details for team members who require access to a system or database.
Records pertaining to the management of a database for electronic data capture (EDC) in a clinical trial.
